<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 16 at 1:57PM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Snow will increase in intensity through late afternoon across
the Berkshires...
Snow will become moderate to heavy at times across the Berkshires
over the next few hours, and continue through late this afternoon.
Snowfall rates could reach up to 1 inch per hour in lower elevations,
and 1 to 2 inches per hour across higher terrain areas mainly
above 1000 feet.
Travel conditions will continue to worsen through this afternoon
due to increasingly snow covered roads and reduced visibilities,
with hazardous travel conditions becoming likely by late
afternoon.</description>
